The paper presents a neural estimator for mutual information that is applicable to a variety of tasks, including generative models and supervised classification. This suggests that the paper could fit into several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information theory (cs.IT), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV). However, given the focus on machine learning and neural networks, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely categories.
